Usage: set_clock_exclusivity [-help] <pin_name> [-exclude_opposite_polarity]
                             [-exclude_related_input_pins]
                             [-exclude_same_polarity] [-group <clock_list>]
                             [-inputs <string>]

-help                          # Prints out the command usage
<pin_name>                     # Name of the pin (string, required)
-exclude_opposite_polarity     # Allows only comparison of the same clock of
                               # the same polarity (bool, optional)
-exclude_related_input_pins    # Allows only comparison of the clock going
                               # through the same input pins of specified gate
                               # (bool, optional)
-exclude_same_polarity         # Allows only comparison of the clock going
                               # through the same launch/capture path
                               # (bool, optional)
-group <clock_list>            # Defines a set of clocks that are exclusive to
                               # the clocks defined in all other groups
                               # (string, optional)
-inputs <string>               # List or collection of input pins for which
                               # clock exclusivity is recognized
                               # (string, optional)